---
title: `$h_t_t_p::header()`
description: Set HTTP headers.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
HTTP::header($key, $value = null);
~~~

**Example:**

~~~ .php
HTTP::header('Expires: Sat, 26 Jul 1997 05:00:00 GMT');
~~~

~~~ .php
HTTP::header('Expires', 'Sat, 26 Jul 1997 05:00:00 GMT');
~~~

~~~ .php
HTTP::header([
    'Expires' => 'Sat, 26 Jul 1997 05:00:00 GMT',
    'Cache-Control' => 'no-cache, must-revalidate'
]);
~~~